@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "arBar" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that arBar runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  The game consists of an 8 by 8 tiles game board on which numbers
are displayed. To play, click on a tile and a bar will appear on
that tile if there is none. If a bar is already there, that bar
will change its state from an ascending type of bar to a descending
type of bar, and vice versa...

  When an adequate number of connections has been made for a bar,
the number shown under that bar will change from black to a colour.
However, this doesn't mean that the connections are correct to
complete the game!... When all tiles have coloured numbers, the
game is completed and arBar will then display a new board to play
with...

  Have fun!

  You can restart the game by clicking on the 'New Game' button.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

